eNCA Senior reporter, Dasen Thathiah filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Police in Umlazi are investigating a shooting that left three sisters dead. They were shot at home by unknown gunmen. Two children, one aged five and another less than a year old were injured, and are in hospital. READ: Search continues for KZN flood victims It's not yet clear what prompted the attack on the family. One of the deceased had just recently buried her stillborn baby. eNCA Senior reporter, Dasen Thathiah shares more details in the video above.